1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:02,140
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:03,240
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,310 --> 00:00:05,310
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:08,050
(Episode 88)

5
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:15,320
Honey,

6
00:00:16,790 --> 00:00:18,490
I've been thinking
about it all night,

7
00:00:19,390 --> 00:00:21,130
and I think Yu Na is right.

8
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:26,260
I've been a nobody my whole life,

9
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:31,240
and I can't ruin
your life and Yu Na's.

10
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:33,710
I'll take responsibility.

11
00:00:34,670 --> 00:00:38,310
I was afraid I'd waver if I saw you,

12
00:00:39,340 --> 00:00:41,210
so I'm leaving this letter instead.

13
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:46,580
Sam Sik, this is wrong.

14
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:48,850
Oh no, this isn't right.

15
00:00:49,450 --> 00:00:50,990
Oh dear.

16
00:00:52,390 --> 00:00:53,390
Right.

17
00:00:54,260 --> 00:00:56,390
I'm the head of this family,

18
00:00:57,230 --> 00:00:58,930
a husband, and a father.

19
00:01:00,670 --> 00:01:01,700
I have to do this.

20
00:01:04,940 --> 00:01:05,940
Mr. Choi!

21
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:10,010
What do you think you're doing?

22
00:01:10,580 --> 00:01:13,240
Are you going to be
Park Tae Ho's lapdog again?

23
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:18,380
Are you planning to give...

24
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:20,080
a false confession
like Park Tae Ho told you to?

25
00:01:20,390 --> 00:01:22,820
You absolutely can't cover up
Park Tae Ho's crimes.

26
00:01:39,140 --> 00:01:40,810
What on earth are you thinking,
Mr. Song?

27
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:45,880
Mom and I are running around
trying to stop Father's arrest,

28
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:51,380
and you're here
leaking information to Min Jun?

29
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:54,150
- I was just...
- How much further...

30
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:57,290
are you going to go to ruin me?

31
00:01:58,020 --> 00:01:59,260
Hyun Jun, please.

32
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:02,390
Isn't it enough that
you've shamed and humiliated me?

33
00:02:03,330 --> 00:02:06,500
I'm trying to become the chairman
of Adele Group as Park Tae Ho's son.

34
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,130
If you can't help, the least
you could do is stay out of my way.

35
00:02:09,730 --> 00:02:10,770
That's enough!

36
00:02:15,210 --> 00:02:16,610
That's uncalled for.

37
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:22,210
If you're so worried,
then stop using him.

38
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:24,380
I wasn't being used!

39
00:02:27,390 --> 00:02:29,920
You're heading down the wrong path,

40
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:32,120
so I was trying to stop you,
even if it meant doing this.

41
00:02:35,330 --> 00:02:37,600
The Adele Group?
What's so important about it?

42
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,030
Is being chairman worth all this?

43
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:44,300
You're committing a crime
to cover for Chairman Park.

44
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,500
If an innocent person gets hurt...

45
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,410
because you covered up
for Chairman Park,

46
00:02:50,380 --> 00:02:52,340
you become the criminal.

47
00:02:59,020 --> 00:03:00,690
Then how should I live?

48
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:03,150
Should I live like you,

49
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,490
as your son?

50
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:08,230
- Park Hyun Jun.
- This!

51
00:03:10,460 --> 00:03:14,070
This is the path I've chosen.
Who are you to decide it's wrong?

52
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:19,040
Both of you, stay out of my way.

53
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,710
Hyun Jun, don't.

54
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,680
I'm sorry.

55
00:03:31,780 --> 00:03:33,020
Our Hyun Jun...

56
00:03:35,790 --> 00:03:37,590
How did he end up like this?

57
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:52,340
The police station.

58
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:54,110
We have to rush down
to the police station.

59
00:03:54,370 --> 00:03:55,370
What's going on?

60
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:58,680
Your dad went to the police station.

61
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:02,450
This isn't right.
We need to drag him back home.

62
00:04:03,450 --> 00:04:06,880
- Oh my.
- Let him be. It was Dad's choice.

63
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:11,360
- What?
- It's the best option right now.

64
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:15,960
It may be the best for you,
but it's not for me.

65
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:19,830
Your father is so frail.

66
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:22,830
He won't survive
that wretched prison life.

67
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:25,240
He'll get sick
and die in there for sure.

68
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:28,040
You're going to deeply regret this
down the road.

69
00:04:28,740 --> 00:04:32,040
If anyone's going to regret this,
it'll be me, so just stay out of it.

70
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:34,480
Oh, for goodness' sake. You brat.

71
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:38,420
My gosh. Honey, oh dear.

72
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:42,090
Sam Sik, oh no. Yu Na's dad!

73
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:45,560
Oh my.

74
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:57,070
You're making a huge mistake.

75
00:04:57,840 --> 00:05:01,010
Don't you realize how serious
Park Tae Ho's crimes are?

76
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:03,010
It wasn't enough...

77
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:05,080
that he killed someone
and covered up the truth.

78
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,640
He tried to kill Jin Ju again...

79
00:05:08,010 --> 00:05:09,450
just because
she tried to expose him.

80
00:05:10,580 --> 00:05:11,580
What?

81
00:05:11,850 --> 00:05:14,720
He tried to kill Jin Ju again?

82
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:17,490
If Park Tae Ho isn't punished,

83
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:20,090
he'll come after Jin Ju again.

84
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:22,360
What did he promise you this time?

85
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:26,700
What did you ask for
to take the fall for Park Tae Ho?

86
00:05:27,370 --> 00:05:29,570
Is it money?
If I give you that money,

87
00:05:29,670 --> 00:05:31,240
will you tell the truth?

88
00:05:32,370 --> 00:05:33,370
No.

89
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:37,840
If it were about money,
I wouldn't have gone this far.

90
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:42,910
It's because Chairman Park
keeps threatening my Yu Na.

91
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:44,920
Ms. Choi?

92
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:50,250
Yes. Chairman Park has a recording
of Yu Na's confession.

93
00:05:51,690 --> 00:05:54,060
He said she'd only be safe
if I took the fall.

94
00:05:56,030 --> 00:05:58,660
How can I send my only daughter
to prison?

95
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,870
I'm her father, after all.

96
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,170
Even if I have to go this far,

97
00:06:04,170 --> 00:06:06,300
I must protect Yu Na's future.

98
00:06:08,610 --> 00:06:09,770
Then what about my life?

99
00:06:12,980 --> 00:06:16,480
What about my life that was ruined
because of Yu Na and Park Tae Ho?

100
00:06:17,650 --> 00:06:19,980
You and Park Tae Ho are the reason
my father was killed.

101
00:06:20,620 --> 00:06:21,920
What about him?

102
00:06:22,690 --> 00:06:24,660
Well, that's...

103
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:27,830
How have you not changed at all
in seven years?

104
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:29,890
How can you still feel...

105
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,260
no remorse?

106
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:39,400
I understand
that you want to protect Ms. Choi.

107
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:43,610
It's natural for a parent to worry
about their child's future.

108
00:06:44,410 --> 00:06:47,350
But you're going about this
the wrong way.

109
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:49,580
If you actually care about Ms. Choi,

110
00:06:50,010 --> 00:06:52,080
you need to right this wrong
here and now.

111
00:06:52,420 --> 00:06:56,290
Covering up one crime only leads
to committing a worse one.

112
00:06:56,620 --> 00:07:00,260
Are you going to turn Ms. Choi
into a monster like Park Tae Ho?

113
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:15,570
What should I do about Choi Sam Sik?

114
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,510
If he's not going to confess,

115
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:19,980
don't let him anywhere near
the police station.

116
00:07:20,810 --> 00:07:23,820
If he changes his mind,
bring him straight to me!

117
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:26,380
Exactly.

118
00:07:27,390 --> 00:07:28,390
Darn.

119
00:07:38,860 --> 00:07:39,860
Mr. Choi.

120
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,700
Take a good look at us
sitting in front of you.

121
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,210
We're victims...

122
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:49,970
who lost our families
because of Park Tae Ho.

123
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:53,110
I lost my father,
and Ms. Kim lost her sister.

124
00:07:54,110 --> 00:07:58,020
And yet, it's so hard for us
to bring Park Tae Ho to justice.

125
00:07:59,580 --> 00:08:03,590
If you help Park Tae Ho,
you're crushing us too.

126
00:08:03,790 --> 00:08:04,790
Just like he did.

127
00:08:04,790 --> 00:08:05,790
What?

128
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,730
Me?

129
00:08:07,790 --> 00:08:10,190
Do you think he's the only bad guy
just because he's a murderer?

130
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,160
Anyone who knows what he did...

131
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:15,370
and looks the other way
is just as bad.

132
00:08:16,730 --> 00:08:17,940
Your hands...

133
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:21,010
are stained
with my father's blood too.

134
00:08:27,010 --> 00:08:28,010
And of course,

135
00:08:28,380 --> 00:08:31,580
the same goes for Ms. Choi.

136
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:34,290
Do you really think...

137
00:08:34,350 --> 00:08:37,050
she'll ever find any peace?

138
00:08:37,260 --> 00:08:40,220
Even if you take the fall
for Park Tae Ho,

139
00:08:40,290 --> 00:08:41,390
this isn't over.

140
00:08:41,630 --> 00:08:43,930
Jin Ju and I are
never going to stop.

141
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:45,800
And Park Tae Ho...

142
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:48,430
will use Ms. Choi again.

143
00:08:48,630 --> 00:08:49,900
And eventually,

144
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,740
Choi Yu Na will
kill someone herself.

145
00:08:54,070 --> 00:08:57,040
Mr. Choi, is that really
what you want?

146
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:17,190
You're right.

147
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:22,370
Even if I go to prison now,
it won't be the end.

148
00:09:24,970 --> 00:09:26,500
A person who's committed a crime...

149
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,710
can never truly run from it.

150
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:32,240
I've also spent...

151
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:34,510
the last seven years
living in terror...

152
00:09:35,780 --> 00:09:37,350
because of what happened.

153
00:09:38,380 --> 00:09:39,420
That was all...

154
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:40,950
because I had the blood...

155
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:44,160
of CEO Baek on my hands.

156
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:47,960
My Yu Na...

157
00:09:49,090 --> 00:09:52,200
shouldn't live her whole life
with blood on her hands.

158
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,470
Mr. Choi...

159
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,670
I'm sorry, Jin Ju.

160
00:10:00,570 --> 00:10:03,410
After everything that happened
to you and CEO Baek,

161
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:06,180
I just blamed Chairman Park...

162
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:08,780
and looked the other way.

163
00:10:09,980 --> 00:10:12,650
I couldn't even bring myself
to look you in the eye.

164
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:18,490
Even so, I lived my life,
blind to my own guilt.

165
00:10:30,330 --> 00:10:32,140
If it's not too late,

166
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:34,510
I'll tell the police the truth.

167
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:39,880
Yes, you've made the right decision.

168
00:10:40,910 --> 00:10:45,320
If you and Yu Na make things right
and accept your punishment,

169
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:50,690
then I will forgive you
and help you.

170
00:10:52,490 --> 00:10:54,490
That's right. That means,

171
00:10:55,730 --> 00:10:57,500
we can all finally be at peace.

172
00:10:57,730 --> 00:10:58,730
Right.

173
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,400
Then I'll go to the police station
right now and...

174
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:05,200
I'm afraid
that's out of the question.

175
00:11:09,610 --> 00:11:12,710
Choi Sam Sik,
Chairman Park wants to see you.

176
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:15,380
What? Chairman Park?

177
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:19,550
No. CEO Choi is going
to the police station.

178
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,650
- Mr. Choi, you should go.
- Sure thing.

179
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:23,890
What...

180
00:11:25,490 --> 00:11:29,290
Darn! This is another
expensive shirt of mine!

181
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:31,460
- Why you...
- You!

182
00:11:35,630 --> 00:11:36,730
Shoot!

183
00:11:39,140 --> 00:11:40,970
Jin Ju, are you okay?

184
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:50,680
I'm here to give a statement.

185
00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:53,020
- Let's get inside right now!
- Sure.

186
00:12:01,330 --> 00:12:03,160
Choi Sam Sik went into
the police station.

187
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:06,300
No, it seems he plans
to give a statement, not confess.

188
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:08,700
What?

189
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:26,050
Are you sure you're okay?
You should really see a doctor.

190
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,890
I'm fine.
I just twisted it a little.

191
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:31,120
Jin Ju.

192
00:12:35,090 --> 00:12:37,260
I heard you got hurt. Are you okay?

193
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:40,900
It's nothing.
Anyway, what about Mr. Choi?

194
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:41,930
Right.

195
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,840
It seems he made it
into the interrogation room.

196
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,570
That's a relief.

197
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:50,340
Right. If CEO Choi tells the truth,

198
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:53,010
Park Tae Ho will be arrested today.

199
00:13:04,260 --> 00:13:06,690
Come on, I told you not to worry.

200
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:09,490
I'm not taking the fall
for Chairman Park.

201
00:13:09,590 --> 00:13:12,600
I'm going to tell the truth
that he ordered everything.

202
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:14,970
Really? But in your letter,

203
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:16,800
you said you were going
to take the fall.

204
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:19,040
I met Jin Ju and we talked.

205
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:23,240
I realized I was wrong.

206
00:13:23,770 --> 00:13:25,110
I need to reveal the truth,

207
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:27,140
so I can live
with a clear conscience.

208
00:13:27,810 --> 00:13:31,380
I think that's what's right
for Yu Na, too.

209
00:13:31,980 --> 00:13:36,590
If I do this, Jin Ju said
she'd actually forgive us and help.

210
00:13:37,450 --> 00:13:38,620
Mr. Choi Sam Sik?

211
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:42,490
I think I'm about to go
into the interrogation room.

212
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:47,200
I'll call you again when I'm done.
Okay, honey.

213
00:13:48,070 --> 00:13:50,370
It won't take too long. Sure.

214
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,500
This way, please.

215
00:14:00,610 --> 00:14:02,510
Oh my, you did the right thing.

216
00:14:03,580 --> 00:14:05,020
You made the right choice.

217
00:14:05,780 --> 00:14:08,290
Since you've changed your mind,

218
00:14:08,350 --> 00:14:10,690
Jin Ju is going to forgive us.

219
00:14:15,630 --> 00:14:18,900
Dad had a change of heart?
What do you mean by that?

220
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:23,100
He said he met Jin Ju
outside the police station.

221
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:27,940
- She persuaded him to testify...
- Is he crazy?

222
00:14:28,470 --> 00:14:30,870
That can't happen.
Do you think he'll be safe...

223
00:14:30,940 --> 00:14:32,410
if he testifies
against Chairman Park?

224
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:34,480
He told me not to worry about that.

225
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,080
Once your father testifies,

226
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:39,580
Park Tae Ho is done for.

227
00:14:39,780 --> 00:14:42,450
Then what about me?
What am I supposed to do?

228
00:14:42,490 --> 00:14:45,490
Dad has to confess
for me to marry Park Hyun Jun.

229
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:46,790
Marry him?

230
00:14:47,860 --> 00:14:48,990
What are you talking about?

231
00:14:49,190 --> 00:14:50,190
Are you saying...

232
00:14:50,930 --> 00:14:52,460
you were planning...

233
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,900
to sell out your own father
to marry into that family?

234
00:14:55,170 --> 00:14:56,230
That's right.

235
00:14:57,230 --> 00:15:00,700
You always told me
that people should be practical.

236
00:15:01,370 --> 00:15:04,170
If Chairman Park falls,
we'll walk away empty-handed.

237
00:15:04,170 --> 00:15:05,910
We won't get anything out of it.

238
00:15:05,910 --> 00:15:07,880
Are you kidding me?

239
00:15:09,310 --> 00:15:12,520
You rotten girl.
You're truly despicable.

240
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:15,720
Curse me all you want.

241
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:19,420
I'm going to convince Dad.
I can't let it end like this.

242
00:15:20,620 --> 00:15:22,730
My gosh. Choi Yu Na!

243
00:15:28,730 --> 00:15:31,140
Oh, my dear husband.

244
00:15:32,370 --> 00:15:34,410
Sam Sik, oh dear.

245
00:15:35,010 --> 00:15:36,070
What do we do?

246
00:15:36,570 --> 00:15:41,480
My gosh.
What am I going to do about this?

247
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:50,920
There's no need to be so nervous.

248
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:02,470
Have a drink
and please wait a moment.

249
00:16:03,030 --> 00:16:04,440
Oh, sure.

250
00:16:27,590 --> 00:16:29,630
I came all the way here
looking for Choi Sam Sik.

251
00:16:30,660 --> 00:16:32,260
But since I'm here,

252
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:35,300
I'm staying to confirm
he actually turns himself in.

253
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:39,500
What?

254
00:16:41,410 --> 00:16:42,670
You're here too?

255
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:44,540
Where's your dad?

256
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:49,250
He went inside to turn himself in
like he was told, right?

257
00:16:50,550 --> 00:16:51,580
Right?

258
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:56,190
What about my dad?

259
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:58,660
I asked you to let me see him
for a moment.

260
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:00,860
I have something
important to tell him...

261
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:02,290
before you interrogate him.

262
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:05,060
That's right. His daughter
has something to tell him.

263
00:17:05,360 --> 00:17:06,700
Please let her.

264
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:10,600
Sit tight. The interrogation
hasn't started yet,

265
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:12,070
so I'll give you a moment.

266
00:17:12,170 --> 00:17:14,170
Okay, thank you.

267
00:17:25,150 --> 00:17:28,450
Mr. Choi Sam Sik, wake up!

268
00:17:33,620 --> 00:17:36,130
Mr. Choi?

269
00:17:36,290 --> 00:17:38,760
Time to wake up. Mr. Choi?

270
00:17:42,230 --> 00:17:45,440
Mr. Choi, wake up!

271
00:17:46,340 --> 00:17:47,340
Dad?

272
00:17:48,010 --> 00:17:50,210
Dad? Dad!

273
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,080
This can't be.

274
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,410
This isn't supposed to happen.

275
00:17:57,780 --> 00:18:00,750
Dad!

276
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:04,860
Dad, please!

277
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:06,860
Dad...

278
00:18:07,460 --> 00:18:08,860
Dad!

279
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:15,630
Dad...

280
00:18:23,340 --> 00:18:24,780
What are you talking about?

281
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:27,880
How did Mr. Choi...
He was at a police station!

282
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:30,210
The intel team
only gave me the basics.

283
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:32,620
I need to go there myself
and find out what happened.

284
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:36,650
If Park Tae Ho was behind this...

285
00:18:43,460 --> 00:18:47,200
Choi Sam Sik never had a backbone.

286
00:18:47,260 --> 00:18:50,900
I'm glad I had
a backup plan for this.

287
00:18:52,140 --> 00:18:54,470
I was in a hurry,
so I did what you said,

288
00:18:54,670 --> 00:18:57,070
but are you sure
about the drug Manager Kang brought?

289
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:59,910
It's untraceable, so don't worry.

290
00:18:59,910 --> 00:19:01,180
Just make sure...

291
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:04,080
the officer who drugged him
stays in line. Got it?

292
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:06,320
Also,

293
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:09,490
don't be stingy
and give him plenty of money.

294
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:11,790
Make sure he keeps his mouth shut.

295
00:19:11,990 --> 00:19:13,560
I'll take care of the cleanup.

296
00:19:14,390 --> 00:19:15,390
Yes, sir.

297
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:19,030
How are you going to clean this up?
Can I really trust you?

298
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:20,930
Unbelievable.

299
00:19:22,070 --> 00:19:23,630
Trust me? You imbecile.

300
00:19:23,630 --> 00:19:26,040
What are you saying?

301
00:19:26,340 --> 00:19:28,110
What about my husband?

302
00:19:28,910 --> 00:19:30,710
How could that be...

303
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:33,510
when he only went
to the police station to testify?

304
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:38,080
Yu Na.

305
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:42,420
They're saying your father is dead.

306
00:19:42,790 --> 00:19:46,460
An autopsy,
or whatever it's called...

307
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:47,930
They told me...

308
00:19:47,930 --> 00:19:51,130
to prepare for the funeral
once it's finished.

309
00:19:51,360 --> 00:19:53,960
I just don't understand
what they're saying.

310
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:58,100
Do the police
make prank calls these days?

311
00:20:01,170 --> 00:20:04,010
Yu Na, didn't you say you were going
to the police station?

312
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:07,010
You saw your father there,
didn't you?

313
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:10,950
He's perfectly fine
and giving his statement, right?

314
00:20:14,890 --> 00:20:17,750
Why are you crying
and stressing me out like this?

315
00:20:18,390 --> 00:20:20,320
Your father must be
at the station right now,

316
00:20:20,390 --> 00:20:22,560
perfectly fine
and finishing up his questioning.

317
00:20:24,090 --> 00:20:28,170
He told me to sit tight,
that he'd be right back!

318
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,700
My gosh. Oh my.

319
00:20:31,870 --> 00:20:34,840
Yu Na. Come on, say something.

320
00:20:35,370 --> 00:20:37,710
Your father's doing fine
down at the police station, right?

321
00:20:38,340 --> 00:20:40,540
Just say it.

322
00:20:40,980 --> 00:20:45,650
Oh no, that's not it.
Take me there right now.

323
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:48,490
I'll go to the police station
and see for myself.

324
00:20:48,650 --> 00:20:50,020
Come on, lead the way!

325
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:53,860
I said hurry up and lead the way!

326
00:20:54,860 --> 00:20:56,560
Oh my.

327
00:20:56,660 --> 00:20:59,860
Mom!

328
00:21:02,630 --> 00:21:03,800
Mom...

329
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,000
What do I do?

330
00:21:06,970 --> 00:21:09,640
Dad...

331
00:21:10,740 --> 00:21:12,580
Mom, what do I do?

332
00:21:16,780 --> 00:21:18,620
(Incoming call:
Chairman Park Tae Ho)

333
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:23,850
(Incoming call:
Chairman Park Tae Ho)

334
00:21:29,860 --> 00:21:31,760
(Incoming call:
Chairman Park Tae Ho)

335
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,640
Honey. By any chance,
did Choi Sam Sik...

336
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:49,080
What's going on?

337
00:21:49,580 --> 00:21:52,280
Here. You should sit with us.

338
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:54,950
It'll be tough for Ms. Choi
on her own,

339
00:21:55,490 --> 00:21:56,890
so you should help her.

340
00:21:58,720 --> 00:21:59,720
Me?

341
00:22:01,190 --> 00:22:03,230
What am I supposed to help with?

342
00:22:08,230 --> 00:22:09,230
Here.

343
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:13,940
This is the last letter
your father left behind.

344
00:22:16,110 --> 00:22:18,240
- What?
- Before turning himself in,

345
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:21,240
he wrote you a letter.

346
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:22,910
He confessed...

347
00:22:24,180 --> 00:22:28,490
to killing his friend Baek Jun Gi
seven years ago,

348
00:22:29,050 --> 00:22:31,660
and he also apologized
to Chairman Park Tae Ho,

349
00:22:32,590 --> 00:22:33,920
who had been under suspicion.

350
00:22:35,130 --> 00:22:36,630
That's exactly what it'll say.

351
00:22:38,760 --> 00:22:40,030
Chairman Park!

352
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:44,570
Your father left that letter
and was heading to turn himself in,

353
00:22:44,940 --> 00:22:47,440
but the extreme stress got to him...

354
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:52,440
and he had a fatal heart attack.

355
00:22:53,210 --> 00:22:55,610
All you have to do is
take that letter...

356
00:22:57,710 --> 00:22:59,750
and hold a press conference.

357
00:23:02,420 --> 00:23:03,420
What is this?

358
00:23:03,990 --> 00:23:05,990
This scene looks awfully familiar.

359
00:23:06,990 --> 00:23:09,160
Are you planning to handle this
just like how you dealt...

360
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:10,930
with Temi Bio seven years ago?

361
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:16,100
Everything was taken care of
so neatly back then, wasn't it?

362
00:23:18,770 --> 00:23:20,870
Since this is Ms. Choi's first time,

363
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:25,940
I need you to help her wrap this up.

364
00:23:37,990 --> 00:23:40,920
What can you do?
It's already happened.

365
00:23:41,830 --> 00:23:43,460
Just be realistic,

366
00:23:43,830 --> 00:23:45,460
and make sure
you get compensated properly.

367
00:23:45,860 --> 00:23:48,830
Ms. Choi, you've always been one
to weigh your options.

368
00:23:55,870 --> 00:23:58,010
Wait, where are you going with that?

369
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:01,380
How could you?

370
00:24:04,780 --> 00:24:06,580
You murdered my dad.

371
00:24:07,550 --> 00:24:09,390
How can you be so shameless?

372
00:24:10,090 --> 00:24:12,890
How can you tell me
to frame him for murder?

373
00:24:12,890 --> 00:24:14,390
How could you do this to me?

374
00:24:15,490 --> 00:24:17,360
You were more than happy...

375
00:24:18,130 --> 00:24:19,300
to push him into it.

376
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:25,870
You drove your own father to become
a murderer and go to prison,

377
00:24:27,070 --> 00:24:28,510
but you think it's unfair
that he died by my hands?

378
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:31,840
Whether he ends up
in prison or the afterlife,

379
00:24:32,180 --> 00:24:35,210
as long as it benefits you,
isn't that all that matters?

380
00:24:37,710 --> 00:24:39,750
But if you still think it's unfair,

381
00:24:40,550 --> 00:24:42,120
and you can't stand it,

382
00:24:42,890 --> 00:24:43,890
then fight back.

383
00:24:45,420 --> 00:24:48,260
Try coming at me
and confronting me like Baek Jin Ju!

384
00:24:50,260 --> 00:24:52,600
That is, if you have what it takes.

385
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:56,100
Of course, if you act out
of foolish pride like your father,

386
00:24:56,830 --> 00:24:58,670
you could end up dead too.

387
00:25:01,270 --> 00:25:02,870
The choice is yours.

388
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:06,780
You can either fight me
and hit rock bottom,

389
00:25:07,540 --> 00:25:10,280
or end this right now
by doing exactly what I say...

390
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:13,020
and save yourself.

391
00:25:24,490 --> 00:25:29,000
Hyun Jun, what's the situation
with the police?

392
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:31,940
With CEO Choi dead,

393
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:34,940
your arrest has been put on hold.

394
00:25:35,310 --> 00:25:36,940
They'll sort this case out first...

395
00:25:38,740 --> 00:25:40,010
and revisit your charges
down the road.

396
00:25:40,010 --> 00:25:41,080
Good.

397
00:25:41,980 --> 00:25:44,180
It looks like
we can wrap this all up soon.

398
00:25:52,420 --> 00:25:54,120
See? I told you it was pointless.

399
00:25:54,690 --> 00:25:57,160
Be realistic and do as you're told.

400
00:26:25,660 --> 00:26:28,790
The Adele Group?
Is being chairman worth all this?

401
00:26:30,590 --> 00:26:33,860
You're committing a crime
to cover for Chairman Park.

402
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,940
If an innocent person gets hurt...

403
00:26:43,940 --> 00:26:46,180
because you covered up
for Chairman Park,

404
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:50,050
you become the criminal.

405
00:27:01,060 --> 00:27:02,490
What's the latest on Mr. Choi?

406
00:27:02,490 --> 00:27:05,300
The police are investigating
the circumstances of his death,

407
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:07,760
and they've decided
to perform an autopsy.

408
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:09,170
After the autopsy,

409
00:27:09,230 --> 00:27:10,900
the body will be returned
to the family,

410
00:27:11,940 --> 00:27:13,000
and they'll hold a funeral.

411
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:14,740
Since it happened at the station,

412
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:17,540
they're leaning toward calling it
a natural death, not a homicide.

413
00:27:17,540 --> 00:27:18,580
No way.

414
00:27:18,980 --> 00:27:21,610
I'm sure
this was Park Tae Ho's doing.

415
00:27:21,850 --> 00:27:24,110
Yes, I was thinking the same thing.

416
00:27:24,210 --> 00:27:25,620
Given the circumstances,

417
00:27:25,620 --> 00:27:26,780
it's highly likely
Mr. Choi was drugged.

418
00:27:27,550 --> 00:27:30,620
What was Park Tae Ho thinking,
pulling a stunt like this?

419
00:27:30,650 --> 00:27:32,590
An investigation could easily
tie him to this.

420
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:35,260
He must've had a way
to handle it discreetly.

421
00:27:35,490 --> 00:27:38,460
Cover-ups and fabrication
are his expertise, aren't they?

422
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:46,700
If he fabricated this incident
as well...

423
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:51,640
He's going to pin the murder
from seven years ago on Mr. Choi.

424
00:27:52,610 --> 00:27:54,640
It's easier to take advantage
of a dead person.

425
00:27:55,310 --> 00:27:58,450
I'll go to the station tomorrow
and check on the situation.

426
00:27:58,850 --> 00:27:59,850
Right.

427
00:28:00,350 --> 00:28:02,220
You should talk to Ms. Choi, too.

428
00:28:02,620 --> 00:28:04,820
Yes. I can't let things play out...

429
00:28:04,890 --> 00:28:06,760
according to Park Tae Ho's plan.

430
00:28:10,490 --> 00:28:11,800
Unbelievable.

431
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:19,540
Honey.

432
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:23,540
Oh my. Honey...

433
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:27,710
Oh, honey. Sam Sik...

434
00:28:29,350 --> 00:28:31,010
What am I going to do?

435
00:28:41,420 --> 00:28:42,430
You vicious girl.

436
00:28:42,890 --> 00:28:44,590
You killed your own father!

437
00:28:47,230 --> 00:28:50,030
My poor husband.

438
00:28:51,130 --> 00:28:52,540
Oh, honey.

439
00:28:54,270 --> 00:28:56,470
Honey, you poor thing.

440
00:29:16,060 --> 00:29:17,460
(Honey…)

441
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:20,830
You decide, Dad.

442
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:24,100
Should we all rot in prison
and lose everything,

443
00:29:24,470 --> 00:29:27,340
or are you going to sacrifice
your insignificant life to save us?

444
00:29:28,070 --> 00:29:29,070
The decision is yours.

445
00:29:30,140 --> 00:29:33,080
I've been a nobody my whole life,

446
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:38,050
and I can't ruin
your life and Yu Na's.

447
00:29:39,620 --> 00:29:41,050
I'll take responsibility.

448
00:29:43,290 --> 00:29:44,390
Dad...

449
00:29:47,060 --> 00:29:48,890
(Honey…)

450
00:29:58,030 --> 00:29:59,670
The choice is yours.

451
00:30:00,370 --> 00:30:02,740
You can either fight me
and hit rock bottom,

452
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:06,210
or end this right now
by doing exactly what I say...

453
00:30:06,310 --> 00:30:08,280
and save yourself.

454
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:22,060
(Seized)

455
00:30:25,700 --> 00:30:26,700
Dad...

456
00:30:27,860 --> 00:30:31,330
Dad, what do I do now?

457
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:34,600
Dad...

458
00:30:54,260 --> 00:30:56,590
Ms. Choi, why did you call
this press conference?

459
00:30:56,730 --> 00:30:58,190
Is Chairman Park the killer?

460
00:30:58,700 --> 00:31:00,430
Why did Mr. Choi Sam Sik die?

461
00:31:00,730 --> 00:31:01,930
I hold...

462
00:31:02,500 --> 00:31:05,070
my father's last letter in my hands.

463
00:31:07,340 --> 00:31:08,400
The true culprit behind...

464
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:10,240
the Temi Bio case
from seven years ago is...

465
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:43,170
(Pearl in Red)

466
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:46,010
How could you protect Park Tae Ho,
the man who killed your father,

467
00:31:46,210 --> 00:31:49,110
and frame your innocent father
as a murderer?

468
00:31:49,350 --> 00:31:50,550
Watch what you say.

469
00:31:50,550 --> 00:31:52,780
Not everyone wants to fight
like you do.

470
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:56,220
Some people care more
about the immediate payoff.

471
00:31:56,290 --> 00:31:58,150
You disgust me.

472
00:31:58,150 --> 00:31:59,990
How could you frame
your own father for murder...

473
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:02,090
just for a quick payout?

474
00:32:02,090 --> 00:32:03,890
The chairmanship at Adele Group...

475
00:32:03,890 --> 00:32:05,660
won't be going to your son,
Park Min Jun.

476
00:32:05,660 --> 00:32:06,960
It's going to be mine.

477
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:08,630
I won't let anyone take it from me.

478
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,000
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
